# Landing Page Guidelines

## Section Order (strict)

1. **Hero** — "One SDK. Any API. Fully typed." + universality subtitle + Get Started / Generate SDK CTAs
2. **CodePreview** — Video showing the SDK in action
3. **Clients** — Company logo carousel (Swiper auto-scroll)
4. **About ("Works everywhere")** — Three cards: Every Framework, Every API Protocol, Every Environment
5. **Features ("How it works")** — Three feature rows: Any API One Interface / Best Type Safety / Generate from OpenAPI
6. **Modules** — Auto-scrolling Swiper carousel of all packages (no static grid)
7. **Blocks ("Faster. Better.")** — HyperFlow, Type Safety, Open Source highlight blocks
8. **Preview ("Meet HyperFlow Devtools")** — Devtools screenshot + CTA (near the end, NOT prominent)
9. **Sponsors** — Sponsor logos
10. **CallToAction** — Final CTA

## Hero Rules

- H1 must be: "One SDK. Any API." with subtitle "Fully Typed." (with wavy underline)
- Subtitle: universality message mentioning REST, GraphQL, Firebase, WebSockets, SSE
- Primary CTA: "Get Started" → docs/getting-started
- Secondary CTA: "Generate SDK" → docs/cli/commands/generate
- Badge link above title: "Generate SDK from Swagger" → CLI docs

## Section Content Rules

### About — "Works everywhere"
- Eyebrow: "Universal by design"
- Three cards with lucide icons: Every Framework, Every API Protocol, Every Environment
- Keep descriptions focused on WHAT the user gets, not technical details

### Features — "How it works"
- Eyebrow: "One interface for everything."
- Three feature rows with alternating graphic/text layout:
  1. Any API, One Interface — CLI SDK demo graphic
  2. Best Type Safety in the Ecosystem — Scan animation graphic
  3. Generate from OpenAPI — AnimatedBeam graphic
- Each has: title, description, "Learn more" link

### Modules
- MUST be an auto-scrolling Swiper carousel, NOT a static grid
- Shows all packages except ESLint
- Continuous loop, no manual swiping needed
- Fade edges with gradient overlays
- "View all integrations" link below

### Preview (Devtools)
- This is NOT a primary selling point — keep it near the end
- Eyebrow: "Power up your development workflow"
- Title: "Meet HyperFlow Devtools"
- Screenshot + CTA to download

## Style Rules

- All section headers use gradient text: `bg-clip-text !text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-zinc-200/60 via-zinc-200 to-zinc-200/60`
- Eyebrow labels use yellow-orange gradient: `from-yellow-500 to-orange-500`
- Use `motion` from `motion/react` for scroll animations (not framer-motion directly)
- All animations should have `viewport={{ once: true }}` to only trigger once
- Primary buttons use yellow gradient, secondary use `shiny-btn` class

## Formatting Rules

- NEVER use em dashes (`—`) anywhere in landing page copy. Use a regular dash (`-`) or rewrite the sentence instead.
